learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-22T22:00:54.819Z",claude-code-agent,"The static describer is kept drift-free by IMPORTING the loader's own normalizers (normalizeCommandName) rather than reimplementing them, and by a keystone parity test asserting describeExtensionBlueprint(bp) deepEquals describeExtensionActivation of the composed+activated bp over a blueprint that exercises every surface. That parity discipline is what surfaced pm-5758: composing the full blueprint with an inline-flags command failed activation under the derived capability set, exposing that deriveExtensionCapabilities omitted schema. Two non-obvious parity rules: (1) a CommandDefinition with inline flags registers a flag target under its OWN path, so flag_commands unions top-level flags keys with inline-flag command names; (2) importer/exporter handler paths are normalizeCommandName('<name> import|export') and land in command_handlers (a superset of commands) but NEVER in command_overrides. The imperative activate escape hatch is invisible to any static reader and is documented as such."
